# Implementation Plan - Separate Sales Leaderboard

Add a dedicated Sales Leaderboard to the Sales Management page, matching the exact UI and logic from the Admin Leaderboard.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The new leaderboard will use the same logic as the admin panel but will be accessible to sales users. I will implement a new backend endpoint specifically for sales users to ensure security and accessibility.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [salesController.js](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/backend/controllers/salesController.js)
- Implement `getSalesLeaderboard` function.
- This will aggregate [Lead](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/backend/controllers/salesController.js#1902-1993) and [Sales](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/backend/controllers/salesController.js#798-904) data to calculate revenue, conversions, and rankings, matching the logic in [adminAnalyticsController.js](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/backend/controllers/adminAnalyticsController.js).

#### [MODIFY] [salesRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/backend/routes/salesRoutes.js)
- Add route: `GET /api/sales/analytics/leaderboard` linked to `getSalesLeaderboard`.

---

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [salesAnalyticsService.js](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/frontend/src/modules/sells/SL-services/salesAnalyticsService.js)
- Add [getLeaderboard(params)](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/frontend/src/modules/admin/admin-services/adminDashboardService.js#47-68) method to call the new backend endpoint.

#### [NEW] [SalesLeaderboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/frontend/src/modules/sells/SL-components/SalesLeaderboard.jsx)
- Create a standalone component that renders the sales leaderboard.
- UI will be a direct port from [Admin_leaderboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/frontend/src/modules/admin/admin-pages/Admin_leaderboard.jsx) (MemberCard, ranking logic, etc.).

#### [MODIFY] [SL_team_management.jsx](file:///c:/Users/AnkitAhirwar/OneDrive/Desktop/Appzeto/frontend/src/modules/sells/SL-pages/SL_team_management.jsx)
- Import and use the `SalesLeaderboard` component as a new section labeled "Sales Leader Board".

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None planned for this UI-centric task.

### Manual Verification
1. **Login as Sales User**: Navigate to the Sales Management (My Team) page.
2. **Verify Leaderboard Display**: Ensure the "Sales Leader Board" section appears at the bottom.
3. **Verify Data Accuracy**: Confirm it matches the rankings seen in the Admin panel (if accessible).
4. **Test Filters**: If any filters (period) are implemented, ensure they update the data correctly.
5. **Check Interaction**: Test the "expand" functionality of member cards to see detailed metrics.
